Push Targets for MediaMTX v1.17.1
==================================

Native in-process stream republishing — push any path to external RTMP,
RTMPS, RTSP, RTSPS, SRT, or HLS (HTTP PUT) destinations without spawning
FFmpeg. Targets are configured per-path in YAML or managed at runtime via
REST API, with automatic retry, status tracking, and cascade prevention.

Based on: bluenviron/mediamtx PR #5558
  "Add push targets feature to rebroadcast a path"
  https://github.com/bluenviron/mediamtx/pull/5558

Differences from upstream PR 5558
----------------------------------

1. Reworked for v1.17.1 (PR 5558 targets main/unreleased)

2. HLS push protocol (not in upstream)
   HTTP PUT of MPEG-TS segments + m3u8 playlist, compatible with
   YouTube/Akamai HLS ingest. IDR-based segment rotation for video,
   PTS-based rotation for audio-only streams.

3. Correctness fixes (not in upstream)
   - SRT/RTSP write/read timeout: default to 30s when unconfigured
     (upstream passes zero → immediate deadline expiry → broken)
   - Audio-only HLS: time-based segment rotation
     (upstream video-only IDR check → unbounded buffer → OOM)
   - segWriter.Initialize() error: checked on segment rotation
     (upstream silently ignores → potential panic/corruption)
   - Manager.Close: parallel target shutdown, mutex released first
     (upstream holds mutex during sequential close → API blocked
     for N × timeout seconds)
   - uploaded slice: copy-on-trim to release old segment data
     (upstream reslice keeps backing array → linear memory leak)
   - TARGETDURATION: tracks actual max segment duration
     (upstream uses configured duration → HLS spec violation when
     GOP > segment duration)
   - Cascade prevention: checks host locality (loopback/localhost),
     not just path name (upstream blocks remote hosts with same path)

4. Scalability (not in upstream) — designed for 500 outputs/path
   - Shared HLS muxer: one MPEG-TS encode per path, segments fanned
     out to subscribers via refcounted immutable segments.
     At 500 outputs: 877 MB/rotation → 1.75 MB (500× reduction).
   - Upload worker pool: bounded concurrency (64 workers) prevents
     thundering herd when all outputs rotate on the same IDR.
   - Channel-based segment delivery: sub-ms upload trigger on segment
     ready, with ticker fallback as heartbeat.

5. FMLE RTMP client (same as upstream)
   Full RTMP publish flow: connect → createStream → FCPublish →
   publish → write. Read goroutine for connection health. Write
   deadline refresh on every frame.

6. Stream notification (same as upstream)
   Channel-based (streamNotify chan struct{}) instead of polling
   for stream availability.

7. Config sync (same as upstream)
   confIDs map distinguishes config-managed vs API-managed targets.
   Config reload only touches conf targets. API changes update
   in-memory config without triggering reload (avoids duplicates).

